{
  "texts": [
    "There are 40 different tags individually applied to every word form.",
    "A ratio of 80:20 is used to divide the dataset into two separate, non-overlapping sections [81].Wikipedia dataset To bootstrap training data, Wikipedia's in isiZulu and Malayalam has been defined.",
    "Due to the former's far larger corpus (65,000 vs. 2,701 articles as of June 2020), it produces a larger training set.",
    "In order to find appropriate named entity tags for articles on Wikipedia they used Graph Knowledge Graph (GKG) [104].",
    "DatasetsRef Type Domain Data size 1 IJCNLP[10], [62], [107] Hindi, Urdu, Marathi Hybrid 14,978 2 ACL Corpus [107] Urdu Hybrid -3 IJCNLP-2008 [21], [78] Sindhi, Hindi Hybrid 11400*5591 4 Wikipedia [104] Malayalam Hybrid 65,000 vs 2,701 articles 5 Google Graph [104] Malayalam Hybrid -6 IJCNLP-08 [93] Hindi, Punjabi Hybrid -7 CoNLL [87] Hindi Deep Learning 2600 phrases 8 NER tagged Corpus [88] Hindi Deep Learning -9 AQMAR Corpus [110] Arabic Deep Learning -10 SiNER [83], [84] Sindhi Arabic Deep Learning -11 ICON 2013 [3] Hindi Machine Learning -12 CC100 [69] Punjabi Machine Learning -13 UNER-1 [72] Urdu Rule-based 5283 entities and 2161 news phrases 14 CANER Corpus [64] Sindhi Arabic Rule-based 72,108 entities and 258,264 words 15 EENAADU, VAARTHA [65] Telugu Rule-based -16 PET [61] -Rule-based -17 CIIL [59] Kannada Rule-based -18 Gazetteers [58] Arabic Rule-based -19 [16] Sindhi Rule-based -20 Tourism [79] Hindi, Urdu, Punjabi Machine Learning -21 CoNLL-2002 [96] Bangla Deep Learning 9,895 unique words UNER dataset Urdu NER dataset which contains large number of Named Entity types that was manually annotated."
